
[1]herpes

   HER'PES,n. [Gr. to creep.] Tetters; an eruption on the skin;
   erysipelas; ringworm, &c. This disease takes various names according to
   its form or the part affected.

   A term applied to several cutaneous eruptions, from their tendency to
   spread or creep from one part of the skin to another.

   An eruption of vesicles in small distinct clusters, accompanied with
   itching or tingling; including the shingles,ringworm, &c.
